@ashkumarverma the `getAccountByHomeId()` API was marked for deprecation as of v3.3.0, but it is still available so it should work unless your project configuration doesn't allow using deprecated functions. MSAL doesn't actually throw an error for this.

You have two options to fix this:
1. (Recommended): Migrate to the new `getAccount()` API:
```javascript

// Sign out user
  function signOut(accountId: string) {
    const account = accountId
      // New getAccount API allows you to pass in a filter
      ? msalInstance.getAccount({ homeAccountId: accountId })
      : null;
    if (account) {
      msalInstance.logoutRedirect({
        account,
      });
      localStorage.clear();
    } else {
      console.error("Account not found");
    }
```

2. Configure your application to ignore the deprecation warning.

